Request Type: MOH Central IT General : Security : Firewall : Polices
Subject: Secuirty Alert #27844
Request Detail: Date/Time Event 2022-06-06 11:12 ASTThreatUnauthorized Access, Modification,or Usage - Unauthorized Usage of SystemsImpactSign of active system compromise,which could lead to a major national incident.Affected Asset78.93.119.80 ?????? ???????? ?????Indicators of Compromise(IOCs)N/ANote: This release does not have an IOC value since the concern is the affected asset itselfMitigation/Detection StepsNCA recommends the following:* Identify and investigate any compromised system for any other infections or abnormalities.* Identify the machine performing the activities and check the logs of the machine.* Perform full scan to identify the root cause of the infection.* Isolate the infected system(s) from the network.* Further investigate the system for any other infections or abnormalities.* Ensure that all systems are installed with latest security updates and patches.* Report findings back to the NCA.Additional InfoNCA has detected sign of compromise on three IP address which belong to "Ministry ofHealth" where the mentioned assets are performing aggressive scan over SSH port (i.e22). The total number of scanned IP addresses were over 105K unique destinationsbetween "2022-06-01" and "2022-06-06" .

Notes: <note date="5/10/22 5:20 pm" author="okhadra" type="tech" time="0" rate="">Assigned to the engineer basil 0537450038</note><note date="5/10/22 10:01 pm" author="Basil.ali@ccs.com.sa" type="tech" time="300" rate="">Dear Iman E-health team Greetings ,As per the site visit and T-shooting we have found the below - Servers network went down after an attempt to connected the diabetic building to core switch through the (Servers Switch ) .- The diabetic building was connected through nano station , and the plan is to change the connectivity to be through newly installed fiber cable . The issue has been resolved Solution : Reconfigure uplinks for Servers Switch and diabetic building switches . and modify vlan routes on core switch . Result : The network is up and running as required. For further support and information please feel free to reach us any time . Thank you RegardsBasil AliNetwork & Security EngineerT : +966 11 4751012 - 4751013 ext 231M:+966 537450038E: Basil.Ali@ccs.com.sa</note>

Notes: <note date="5/9/22 11:02 pm" author="Basil.ali@ccs.com.sa" type="tech" time="0" rate="">Dear E-Health Team Greetings , We have tried to call you on ( Eng.Sami +966508888259)and (Eng.Basim +966549736746) to arrange the site visit but our calls went unanswered.Please provide an available contact number of if you would like to schedule a callback please mention below : Callback Date : Callback Time : Thank you RegardsBasil AliNetwork & Security EngineerT : +966 11 4751012 - 4751013 ext 231M:+966 537450038E: Basil.Ali@ccs.com.sa </note><note date="5/9/22 8:37 pm" author="okhadra" type="tech" time="0" rate="">Assigned to the engineer basil 0537450038</note><note date="5/10/22 3:31 pm" author="Basil.ali@ccs.com.sa" type="tech" time="0" rate="">Dear E-Health Team As per the The site visit we have found the below issues . 1 - Xray department switches :VTP Protocol was functioning as a server  and prevent VLAN communications . Solution : Configure VTP Protocol mode transparent . 2- Old OPD department : The switch up link was configured as an access port . which causing the port to be flapping up down Solution : Reconfigure the up link to be trunk interface , from switch side and core side . 3- PACS servers keep on disconnecting . Solution : The uplink between the PACs rack and core switch  was configured as a trunk from one side and access from other . Solution : Reconfigure the up link between the PACs rack and core switch to be trunk . as check the network now is stable . For further support and information .please feel free to reach us any time . RegardsBasil AliNetwork & Security EngineerT : +966 11 4751012 - 4751013 ext 231M:+966 537450038E: Basil.Ali@ccs.com.sa</note>

Basil 0537450038</note><note date="3/16/22 12:45 pm" author="Basil.ali@ccs.com.sa" type="tech" time="0" rate="">Dears RUH-RAIN-IT TeamGreetings ,in order to proceed further with this case please provide us the below commands output result from any PC that you noticed the slowness,  ,Navigate to Start menu and type ( CMD ) then press enter,a new black window will appear then execute the below commands,-pathping -q 255 10.0.64.100   <--- it will take around 10 minutes to calculate the result-pathping -q 255 8.8.8.8          <--- it will take around 10 minutes to calculate the result- tracert 10.0.64.100  <--- it will take around 5 minutes to calculate the result- tracert 8.8.8.8          <---- it will take around 5 minutes to calculate the result- ipconfig /allAwaiting your feedbackThank youRegardsBasil AliNetwork & Security EngineerT : +966 11 4751012 - 4751013 ext 231M:+966 537450038E: Basil.Ali@ccs.com.sa</note><note date="3/22/22 4:54 pm" author="Basil.ali@ccs.com.sa" type="tech" time="0" rate="">Dears RUH-RAIN-IT TeamAs there is no response received from your end, and we cannot keep the ticket inactive for a long time, I will proceed to close this ticket for now, and you are welcome to reply back on this case within two working days or open a new case on your suitable time. Thank you RegardsBasil AliNetwork & Security EngineerT : +966 11 4751012 - 4751013 ext 231M:+966 537450038E: Basil.Ali@ccs.com.sa</note>

Notes: <note date="3/7/22 10:00 am" author="okhadra" type="tech" time="0" rate="">assigned to Eng. Bilal 0543659545</note><note date="3/7/22 3:03 pm" author="Bilal" type="tech" time="60" rate="">Dear Muhammad,As per our discussion, please find our report here:*Issue Description:*WAN services stopped during STC IPVPN circuit went down which means that the backup router didn't handle the traffic. *Finding:*We checked the network after the STC link returned back up again, and checked the routing table on the firewall but found some routes entries are going through of the nexthop 10.189.247.205 and others are going through of  the nexthop 10.189.247.206. *Conclusions* * All routes advertised from dual-homing routers should be identical from both routers . In other words, all routes should go to one nexthop only at the same time . * The configuration on both ISPs routers need to be reviewed and tested during a meeting between them, to confirm the below:* The routing advertisement is identical on both. * Reachability on both to MOH services. * High availability configuration. * Please arrange a meeting between both ISPs to check and fix the issue.Regards,Bilal Abu-Arja0543659545</note>

Notes: <note date="3/6/22 1:34 pm" author="Basil.ali@ccs.com.sa" type="tech" time="0" rate="">Dear Abdulrahman As per the T-shooting, I have found that many connections to MOH DNS 10.0.64.100 Are blocked through the Enabled IPS. It's called false-positive connections, which firewall blocked it sometimes and permit it some times. because of that many websites will not work while the firewall is blocking DNS traffic, And for the maintenance application ( asset ultimate pro system ) it's using a blocked port 1433 toward the internet. Alongside with port 80 Solution : - Configure an exception for DNS queries to IP 10.0.64.100.- Configure an exception for Asset ultimate pro system.For further support and information please feel free to reach us any time. Thank you RegardsBasil AliNetwork & Security EngineerT : +966 11 4751012 - 4751013 ext 231M:+966 537450038E: Basil.Ali@ccs.com.sa</note><note date="3/6/22 1:02 pm" author="okhadra" type="tech" time="0" rate="">Assigned to Eng. Basil 0537450038</note>

Notes: <note date="2/6/22 5:03 pm" author="Basil.ali@ccs.com.sa" type="tech" time="0" rate="">Dear Eng.Abdulaziz , As per our phone discussion, you have mentioned that the services are working only for IP address 10.196.96.0/24 as we have tested. In order to solve this issue, you need to contact KFSH and confirm with them that they are permitting the network 10.196.96.0/19 instead of 10.196.96.0/24 to reach the services, for now, every device on the network 10.196.96.0/24 will be able to access the services through local Host file resolving.Thank you RegardsBasil AliNetwork & Security EngineerT : +966 11 4751012 - 4751013 ext 231M:+966 537450038E: Basil.Ali@ccs.com.jo </note><note date="2/6/22 4:45 pm" author="Basil.ali@ccs.com.sa" type="tech" time="0" rate="">Dear IT team , Greetings , As per the T-shooting and phone discussion with Engineer Abdulaziz , we have found that you are assigning static DNS 10.241.128.2 To the devices that required a connection with KFMC and the reason why the service( https://kfmc-uvzfp.kfmc.med/ZFP ) is not working that is the DNS is not reachable as per the screenshots we have attempted to resolve another websites such as google.com and moh.gov.sa but it failed Solutions : 1- Contact KFMC to duple check the permitted subnet through their firewall, it should be 10.196.96.0/19 and to permit the reachability of the DNS Server so you will be able to resolve the local services.or 2- Configure the host file on all windows machines  the required connectivity to KFMC as follows Navegate the path :C:\Windows\System32\drivers\etc ---> Edit file (Host)Copy and paste the below lines to the bottom of the text file and then save it . 10.241.128.19	KFMC-RISDB.kfmc.med10.241.128.41	KFMC-RISWEB.kfmc.med10.241.128.42	KFMC-RISVRC.kfmc.med10.240.130.217	KFMC-UVZFP.kfmc.med10.240.130.60 	KFMC-ZFP01.kfmc.medFor further support and information, please feel free to reach us. Thank you RegardsBasil AliNetwork & Security EngineerT : +966 11 4751012 - Notes: <note date="2/2/22 12:17 am" author="Basil.ali@ccs.com.sa" type="tech" time="0" rate="">Dear KSH E-Health Team Greetings , The issue has been resolved and the server is reachable now elnet@RYD-SALMAN-ER-C1#traceroute 10.105.103.101Type Control-c to abortSending DNS Query to 10.0.64.100Type Control-c to abortTracing the route to IP node (10.105.103.101) from 1 to 30 hops  1    <1 ms    1 ms   <1 ms 10.100.103.1  2     1 ms    1 ms    1 ms 10.105.103.101telnet@RYD-SALMAN-ER-C1#telnet@RYD-SALMAN-ER-C1#*ping 10.105.103.101*Sending 1, 16-byte ICMP Echo to 10.105.103.101, timeout 5000 msec, TTL 64Type Control-c to abort_Reply from 10.105.103.101  : bytes=16 time=2ms TTL=254_Success rate is 100 percent (1/1), round-trip min/avg/max=2/2/2 ms.telnet@RYD-SALMAN-ER-C1#As per the T-shooting , I've found that the connectivity between PACs systems DC and hospital network relies on static route only, and checked the routing table and found the route to network 10.105.103.0 is not exist ,Solution : Configure a new static route on core switches toward PACS Network Gateway as follwoing : ip route 10.105.103.0/24 10.42.131.5For further support and information, please feel free to reach us . Thank you RegardsBasil AliNetwork & Security EngineerT : +966 11 4751012 - 4751013 ext 231M:+966 537450038E: Basil.Ali@ccs.com.jo  </note><note date="2/1/22 9:16 pm" author="hzarqa" type="tech" time="0" rate="">Assigned to Eng. Basil Ali 0537450038</note>
